divs: sighting detailsi am just back from vacation in tucson arizona. while there my sister and i saw a ufo that looked like an on comming airplane at night but that dropped two "star like " objects that were under someones control as the first one dropped and hovered, then went east a ways then turned back west again and quickly came back to where it was. since this report is not about that, i will refer you to the report i made from tucson to you. submitted jan 5th 2011. i talked to a gentleman from mufon in arizona about this sighting, and during the conversation mentioned this sighting from the internet on a web cam set up in the middle of no where. i am submitting the screen shot of what i got. the gentleman asked me to send it in when i got back to texas so i am doing so. it appears that this was takin back in 2003 about the time i got my first computer. i stumbled upon the fact that there were web cams set up over the world and some in weird places, this one was in a remote location but i dont know where. as well the original picture looked a bit sharper to me but you can zoom in and see that it does not look like a plane. this web cam took still shots once every minute, at first nothing was there, then in the next shot it was. i am in no way making a claim that this object is extra terrestrial. but for this sighting and the one in tucson, i have never seen anything in the sky i could not identify. in any case i wanted to follow thru and send in the screen shot of a printed page and picture. i wish i had kept the screen shot and not printed it, as it adds grain to the shot. i will search my old computer that was used then and try to find the original if i can. thanks, *(wit's name deleted--cms\sg).
Summary: UFO spotted on a web cam
